setSymbol

public void setSymbol(int[] xc,
                      int[] yc,
                      int np)
The symbol is defined by a polygon. The polygon is defined by a series of points (x,y). These points are connected in succession to form the outline of the symbol. These x and y points are such that 0 <= x,y < 25. In other words an area of 25 X 25 is used for the initial definition. This would be the size of the bounding box for this polygon.

Parameters:
xc - Array of x co-ordinates 0 <= x < 25
yc - Array of y co-ordinates 0 <= y < 25
